\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Starfish pipeline with unit-disk target. The $27$ highlighted triangles fill one arm of the physical starfish (\subref  {fig:star-clean}). Column\nobreakspace  {}2 is the \emph  {no-shape-opt path}: Tutte lays the arm's boundary vertices onto a thin angular wedge of the disk (\subref  {fig:star-tutte}), producing an inward sliver fan, and Winslow transports that fan back to the physical arm (\subref  {fig:star-winslow-from-tutte}) where it unwinds into a decent radial fan of moderate-aspect-ratio triangles. Column\nobreakspace  {}3 is the \emph  {with-shape-opt path}: shape optimization (\subref  {fig:star-opt}) compresses the wedge slightly but cannot reshape its sliver structure with the boundary pinned; Winslow then transports the polished wedge back to a similar radial fan (\subref  {fig:star-winslow}). Shape-opt's contribution is a modest improvement of the worst element on the physical mesh ($\min |J|$ $0.0011\!\to \!0.0026$), not a qualitative change; Winslow does most of the work.\relax }}{16}{figure.caption.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:star-pipeline}{{10}{16}{Starfish pipeline with unit-disk target. The $27$ highlighted triangles fill one arm of the physical starfish (\subref {fig:star-clean}). Column~2 is the \emph {no-shape-opt path}: Tutte lays the arm's boundary vertices onto a thin angular wedge of the disk (\subref {fig:star-tutte}), producing an inward sliver fan, and Winslow transports that fan back to the physical arm (\subref {fig:star-winslow-from-tutte}) where it unwinds into a decent radial fan of moderate-aspect-ratio triangles. Column~3 is the \emph {with-shape-opt path}: shape optimization (\subref {fig:star-opt}) compresses the wedge slightly but cannot reshape its sliver structure with the boundary pinned; Winslow then transports the polished wedge back to a similar radial fan (\subref {fig:star-winslow}). Shape-opt's contribution is a modest improvement of the worst element on the physical mesh ($\min |J|$ $0.0011\!\to \!0.0026$), not a qualitative change; Winslow does most of the work.\relax }{figure.caption.15}{}}
